# 🍬 Nassau Candy Distributor Profitability Analysis

## 📖 Project Description
This project was developed as part of the **Data Analysis Internship at Unified Mentor**. It focuses on analyzing the profitability of products sold by Nassau Candy Distributor using Python. The project transforms raw sales data into meaningful business insights to help identify profitable products, margin risks, and opportunities for better decision-making.

## 🎯 Problem Statement
The organization lacks visibility into:
- Which product lines generate the highest gross margin.
- Whether high-sales products are actually profitable.
- How profitability varies across product divisions.
- Which products represent margin risk.

## 🎯 Objectives
- Analyze sales and gross profit performance.
- Calculate Gross Margin Percentage.
- Identify top-performing and low-performing products.
- Detect pricing inefficiencies.
- Provide actionable business insights through data analysis.

## 📂 Dataset
**Dataset:** Nassau Candy Distributor Sales Data (CSV)

## 🛠️ Technologies Used
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Streamlit (Dashboard)
- VS Code

## 📊 Key Features
- Data Cleaning & Preprocessing
- Gross Margin % Calculation
- Product-wise Profitability Analysis
- Sales vs Profit Comparison
- Margin Risk Identification
- Interactive Dashboard using Streamlit

## 📈 Business Insights
- Identified the most profitable product categories.
- Highlighted products with high sales but low profit margins.
- Detected pricing inefficiencies.
- Compared profitability across different product divisions.

